# Mantismo Commercial License

This document summarises the terms under which a commercial license for
Mantismo is available. A commercial license is required if your use is
incompatible with the AGPL-3.0 (see LICENSE).

## When You Need a Commercial License

You need a commercial license if you:

- Embed Mantismo in a proprietary product distributed to customers
- Offer Mantismo (or a product built on it) as a hosted or managed service
  without making your complete source code available under AGPL-3.0
- Use Mantismo internally in a commercial organisation and are not able
  to comply with the AGPL-3.0 source disclosure requirements

You do **not** need a commercial license if you:

- Use Mantismo for personal, non-commercial purposes
- Use Mantismo in an open-source project licensed under AGPL-3.0
- Evaluate Mantismo internally before purchasing

## What a Commercial License Grants

- The right to use, modify, and distribute Mantismo in proprietary products
- The right to offer Mantismo as part of a hosted service without AGPL-3.0
  source disclosure obligations
- No copyleft requirements on your surrounding code
- Access to commercial support (as agreed per contract)

## What a Commercial License Does Not Grant

- The right to sub-license Mantismo to third parties
- Ownership of the Mantismo trademark or brand
- Rights to any future proprietary enterprise components (licensed separately)

